summary:
#'I'm volatile and don't play well with others' #now just imagine tony meeting jessica jones ....

  they’d despise each other....
body:
#‘I’m volatile and don’t play well with others’ #now just imagine tony meeting jessica jones ….

they’d despise each other. she’d call him offensive names with special digs at his past womanizing and rich-boy lifestyle, he’d make fun of her broody “schtick” and intentionally push her buttons to make her “lighten up,” and people would fight to keep the two of them apart. then he’d find out about her alcoholism and she’d flinch when she learned his parents died in a violent car accident. they’d suddenly, begrudgingly, be less hostile towards each other. he’d try to get her help with her alcoholism, becoming something of a male trish but with more of her traits and understanding her much better and at the same time less. he’d still rub her the wrong way, they’d never become great friends, but if she was in a bar at any time and heard someone badmouthing him the way she used to do to his face, she’d probably backhand them across the room and finish their drink.

title: country boy!peter with city slicker!tony
body:
(i live in the middle of nowhere and i like to pretend that my life is interesting, sorry. also, all of these come from personal experience so they’re 100% realistic)

  • it’s 2019 and tony can’t believe horse shit in the street is an actual problem he has to deal with??
  • peter is used to the smell of manure in the spring, but the first time that tony smells it he throws up in the yard
  • tony is super frustrated about the fact that the closest gas station is a 15 minute drive from their house 
  • tony: “why are there 10 different churches here?? there’s only 1,000 people!!!???”
  • tony hates driving on gravel roads because they’re dusty and bumpy and “not safe at all!”
  • the first time that tony watched peter prep a chicken after killing it he was both impressed and terrified
  • tony refuses to go into the woods on their property during deer season even though they have no trespassing signs and peter bought him plenty of fluorescent orange clothes which makes him look ridiculous
  • tony hates peter’s old truck with a passion because it’s constantly breaking down but peter refuses to get a new one because he knows how to fix it every time it breaks down. 
  • tony going grocery shopping in town and having the cashier tell him that she doesn’t agree with his lifestyle. he’s shocked but realizes arguing with a 60 year old woman isn’t worth it, but he was really close to fighting her
  • peter’s accent gets really noticeable when he’s excited
  • the first time peter catches tony saying “y’all” he teases him about it for weeks
  • the constant debate over whether “y’all’re” (y’all are) is a word.

title: The Busted Ankle
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2SElrXx

by LMDrums

“I was wondering if we could go get some breakfast,” Peter suggested, “There is this new restaurant down the street. It’s within walking distance.”

Tony gritted his teeth at the idea of walking. He could barely move around the lab without extreme pain. He didn’t want to worry the kid, but he was going to have to pull off a hell of an acting job to fool him.

“Yeah… that sounds fun,” Tony replied. He almost couldn’t believe himself. He couldn’t walk that far.

–or–

Tony breaks his ankle while in the lab but neglects to tell anyone. Peter comes over and eventually finds out the truth.
